{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.18",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 18,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 18",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 18 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:1",
      "text": "Then answered Bildad the Shuhite, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:2",
      "text": "How long will it be ere ye make an end of words? mark, and afterwards we will speak.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:3",
      "text": "Wherefore are we counted as beasts, and reputed vile in your sight?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:4",
      "text": "He teareth himself in his anger: shall the earth be forsaken for thee? and shall the rock be removed out of his place?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:5",
      "text": "Yea, the light of the wicked shall be put out, and the spark of his fire shall not shine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:6",
      "text": "The light shall be dark in his tabernacle, and his candle shall be put out with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:7",
      "text": "The steps of his strength shall be straitened, and his own counsel shall cast him down.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:8",
      "text": "For he is cast into a net by his own feet, and he walketh upon a snare.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:9",
      "text": "The gin shall take him by the heel, and the robber shall prevail against him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:10",
      "text": "The snare is laid for him in the ground, and a trap for him in the way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:11",
      "text": "Terrors shall make him afraid on every side, and shall drive him to his feet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:12",
      "text": "His strength shall be hungerbitten, and destruction shall be ready at his side.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:13",
      "text": "It shall devour the strength of his skin: even the firstborn of death shall devour his strength.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:14",
      "text": "His confidence shall be rooted out of his tabernacle, and it shall bring him to the king of terrors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:15",
      "text": "It shall dwell in his tabernacle, because it is none of his: brimstone shall be scattered upon his habitation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:16",
      "text": "His roots shall be dried up beneath, and above shall his branch be cut off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:17",
      "text": "His remembrance shall perish from the earth, and he shall have no name in the street.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:18",
      "text": "He shall be driven from light into darkness, and chased out of the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:19",
      "text": "He shall neither have son nor nephew among his people, nor any remaining in his dwellings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:20",
      "text": "They that come after him shall be astonied at his day, as they that went before were affrighted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.18.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 18:21",
      "text": "Surely such are the dwellings of the wicked, and this is the place of him that knoweth not God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
